<Worksheet ss:Name="Notes"><Table>
<Row><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">Notes</Data></Cell></Row>
<Row><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">The JMTES coefficient is measured in absence percentage points relative to JES.</Data></Cell></Row>
<Row><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">No-covariate models regress each absence percentage outcome on the JMTES indicator using overlap weights.</Data></Cell></Row>
<Row><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">Covariate-adjusted models add grade, female, Black, age, meal-status code, and entry code.</Data></Cell></Row>
<Row><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">Overlap weights are 1 - propensity score for JMTES students and propensity score for JES students.</Data></Cell></Row>
<Row><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">Percentage outcomes are used because JMTES was reported through 159 school days and JES through 170 school days.</Data></Cell></Row>
</Table></Worksheet>
